-- Fed Tapering, U.S. Budget, Syria, DJIA: Week Sept. 14-21
-- B y   D i c k   S c h u m a c h e r ,   G r e g   M i l e s   a n d   J i m   M c D o n a l d
-- 2013-09-16T04:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-12/fed-tapering-u-s-budget-syria-djia-week-ahead-sept-14-21.html
The U.S. Federal Open Market
Committee probably will decide in the coming week to begin
tapering its $85 billion of monthly bond purchases as the
world’s largest economy maintains its expansion, according to a
Bloomberg survey.  U.S. Congress  may vote on a stopgap funding bill to keep
the government functioning through Dec. 15 as House Republican
leaders move to avert a possible shutdown by satisfying demands
of some party factions.  Goldman Sachs Group Inc., Visa Inc. and Nike Inc. will be
added to the  Dow Jones Industrial Average . German politicians
end their last day of campaigning before the general election.  Europe’s Champions League club soccer tournament will kick
off, with Bayern Munich favored by bookmakers to keep its title.  MONDAY, Sept. 16  To contact the reporters on this story:
